s, executors, and other background resources.\\n- Keep existing tests unchanged; new coverage was added in a separate test class.\\n\\n## Progress\\n### Done\\n- [x] Earlier/superseded attempt replaced placeholder test in `tests/src/org.apache.maven/maven-aether-provider/3.0/src/test/java/org_apache_maven/maven_aether_provider/Maven_aether_providerTest.java`.\\n- [x] Earlier/superseded attempt added tests covering:\\n  - `MavenRepositorySystemSession` inherited configuration behavior.\\n  - `DefaultServiceLocator` service wiring.\\n  - `DefaultVersionRangeResolver` metadata parsing/range filtering.\\n  - `DefaultVersionResolver` handling of `RELEASE`, `LATEST`, and timestamped snapshots.\\n  - `VersionsMetadataGeneratorFactory` and `SnapshotMetadataGeneratorFactory`.\\n- [x] Removed JUnit `@TempDir` usage after `/tmp` failures and now writes metadata XML under `build/generated-test-metadata/`.\\n- [x] Fixed latest/release vs snapshot metadata collision by splitting metadata files and resolving by artifact ID plus requested metadata version.\\n- [x] Removed premature `RemoteSnapshotMetadataGenerator.transformArtifact(snapshot)` assertion that caused NPE in Maven 3.0.\\n- [x] User reported the previous feature test did not pass and requested a different uncovered `org.apache.maven:maven-aether-provider:3.0` feature.\\n- [x] Added new file `tests/src/org.apache.maven/maven-aether-provider/3.0/src/test/java/org_apache_maven/maven_aether_provider/DefaultArtifactDescriptorReaderTest.java`.\\n- [x] New test covers `DefaultArtifactDescriptorReader.readArtifactDescriptor` via public API.\\n- [x] New test uses in-memory stubs:\\n  - `RecordingVersionResolver`\\n  - `RecordingArtifactResolver`\\n  - `StaticRemoteRepositoryManager`\\n  - `RecordingModelBuilder`\\n  - `SimpleModelBuildingResult`\\n- [x] New test verifies conversion of an effective Maven `Model` into an Aether artifact descriptor:\\n  - version resolver request and POM artifact request.\\n  - `ModelBuildingRequest` settings: `ModelBuildingRequest.VALIDATION_LEVEL_MINIMAL`, `isProcessPlugins() == false`, `isTwoPhaseBuilding() == false`, non-null `ModelSource`, non-null `ModelResolver`.\\n  - project repository `project-repo` and URL `https://repo.example.test/project`.\\n  - release/snapshot repository policies.\\n  - dependency `com.acme.libs:api:2.1` with `jar`, `runtime`, optional `true`.\\n  - exclusion `com.acme.excluded:legacy` with wildcard classifier/extension.\\n  - managed dependency `com.acme.platform:bom-entry:3.0`.\\n  - license properties including `license.count`, `license.0.name`, `license.0.url`, `license.0.comments`, and `license.0.distribution`.\\n- [x] Made existing placeholder top-level class `Maven_aether_providerTest` public without changing its test method logic.\\n- [x] Investigated Native Image `/tmp` failure:\\n  - initial failure: `Fatal error: Unable to create temp directory for prefix driverRoot-: java.nio.file.FileSystemException: No space left on device`.\\n  - adding only `-Djava.io.tmpdir=...` did not help because Native Image creates `driverRoot-*` before that property takes effect.\\n  - adding `environment.put(\\\"TMPDIR\\\", ...)`, `TMP`, and `TEMP` failed because `BuildNativeImageTask` has no `environment` property.\\n- [x] Removed invalid `environment` configuration after failure:\\n  - `Could not get unknown property 'environment' for task ':nativeTestCompile' of type org.graalvm.buildtools.gradle.tasks.BuildNativeImageTask.`\\n- [x] Updated `tests/src/org.apache.maven/maven-aether-provider/3.0/build.gradle` to configure Native Image JVM temp dir with:\\n  - `File nativeTmpDir = layout.buildDirectory.dir(\\\"native-tmp\\\").get().asFile`\\n  - `tasks.named(\\\"nativeTestCompile\\\") { doFirst { nativeTmpDir.mkdirs() } }`\\n  - `buildArgs(\\\"-J-Djava.io.tmpdir=${nativeTmpDir.absolutePath}\\\")`\\n\\n### In Progress\\n- [ ] Awaiting external rerun of `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.apache.maven:maven-aether-provider:3.0` after adding `DefaultArtifactDescriptorReaderTest.java` and the Native Image temp-dir build arg.\\n\\n### Blocked\\n- No current code blocker known.\\n- External environment still reports `/tmp`/shared-memory space warnings, but current build file now attempts to route Native Image JVM temp creation to `build/native-tmp`.\\n\\n## Key Decisions\\n- **Avoid `@TempDir`**: JUnit attempted to create temp dirs under `/tmp`, which failed with `java.nio.file.FileSystemException: /tmp/junit...: No space left on device`.\\n- **Use module-local generated metadata files**: Metadata XML is written to `build/generated-test-metadata/` to avoid `/tmp`.\\n- **Use a `RecordingMetadataResolver` stub**: Exercises Maven Aether resolvers via public `MetadataResolver` API while controlling metadata inputs.\\n- **Split release/latest and snapshot metadata**: Maven 3.0 `DefaultVersionResolver` threw `StringIndexOutOfBoundsException` when snapshot metadata was used for `RELEASE`/`LATEST`.\\n- **Do not assert transformed remote snapshot version directly**: `RemoteSnapshotMetadataGenerator.transformArtifact(snapshot)` threw NPE before merge-populated snapshot metadata existed.\\n- **Switch to different uncovered feature**: User reported the previous feature test did not pass, so new coverage targets `DefaultArtifactDescriptorReader` instead.\\n- **Keep new feature test self-contained**: The new test uses in-memory public API stubs and does not start servers, clients, executors, or background resources.\\n- **Use `-J-Djava.io.tmpdir=...` for Native Image driver**: `-Djava.io.tmpdir=...` alone is too late for Native Image’s own `driverRoot-*` temp directory creation.\\n- **Do not use `BuildNativeImageTask.environment`**: It caused `Could not get unknown property 'environment' for task ':nativeTestCompile' of type org.graalvm.buildtools.gradle.tasks.BuildNativeImageTask.`\\n\\n## Next Steps\\n1. Rerun external test command: `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.apache.maven:maven-aether-provider:3.0`.\\n2. If compilation fails, inspect `DefaultArtifactDescriptorReaderTest.java` first, especially Aether 1.7 API signatures around `RemoteRepository.getPolicy(...)`, `DefaultArtifactTypeRegistry.add(...)`, and `ModelBuildingResult`.\\n3. If Native Image still fails with `Fatal error: Unable to create temp directory for prefix driverRoot-: java.nio.file.FileSystemException: No space left on device`, verify the final command line includes `-J-Djava.io.tmpdir=.../build/native-tmp`.\\n4. If new test logic fails, adjust only the new `DefaultArtifactDescriptorReaderTest.java` unless a missing dependency/runtime argument is truly required.\\n5. Keep tests Native Image-compatible and avoid skip guards.\\n\\n## Critical Context\\n- Test file path from earlier/superseded attempt: `tests/src/org.apache.maven/maven-aether-provider/3.0/src/test/java/org_apache_maven/maven_aether_provider/Maven_aether_providerTest.java`\\n- New test file path: `tests/src/org.apache.maven/maven-aether-provider/3.0/src/test/java/org_apache_maven/maven_aether_provider/DefaultArtifactDescriptorReaderTest.java`\\n- Build file path: `tests/src/org.apache.maven/maven-aether-provider/3.0/build.gradle`\\n- Dynamic access report read during new work:\\n  - `tests/src/org.apache.maven/maven-aether-provider/3.0/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json`\\n  - `\\\"hasDynamicAccess\\\" : false`\\n  - `\\\"classes\\\" : [ ]`\\n- Previous failure 1: all tests failed because `@TempDir` could not create `/tmp/junit...`: `No space left on device`.\\n- Previous failure 2: `metadataGeneratorFactoriesCreateVersionAndSnapshotMetadataThroughPublicInterfaces()` failed with:\\n  - `java.lang.NullPointerException: Cannot invoke \\\"org.apache.maven.artifact.repository.metadata.SnapshotVersion.getVersion()\\\" because the return value of \\\"java.util.Map.get(Object)\\\" is null`\\n  - at `RemoteSnapshotMetadata.getExpandedVersion(RemoteSnapshotMetadata.java:102)`\\n- Previous failure 3: `versionResolverHandlesReleaseL